  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nHello! I help maintain [eth-gas-reporter][1]. \r\n\r\nAm [cross-posting recent issues opened there][2] that v5.4.25 has changed expectations about how truffle loads 3rd party mocha reporters. \r\n\r\nPrior to that version, when someone defined a reporter in truffle.config.js's mocha options it was used by default.\r\n\r\nWith 5.4.25, the `--reporter` cli flag is the only way to select a reporter other than `spec`. \r\n\r\nA workaround for eth-gas-reporter users is to use the cli flag:\r\n```\r\ntruffle test --reporter eth-gas-reporter\r\n```\r\n\r\n[1]: https://github.com/cgewecke/eth-gas-reporter\r\n[2]: https://github.com/cgewecke/eth-gas-reporter/issues/268\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n+ truffle unbox metacoin\r\n+ yarn add eth-gas-reporter\r\n+ configure `truffle.config.js` with:\r\n  ```js \r\n  mocha: {\r\n    reporter: \"eth-gas-reporter\"\r\n  }\r\n  ```\r\n+ run `truffle test`\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nThere should be a table with gas readings for each deployment and method invocation at the end of the suite\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nNo table\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Mac OSX\r\n* Ethereum client: ganache-cli latest\r\n* Truffle version (`5.4.25`):\r\n* node version (`14`):\r\n",
